# This file keeps the backgrounds directory in git

## For Local Images:

To use local images instead of downloading from internet:

1. Create an `images/` subfolder here
2. Add your wallpaper files:
   - `default.jpg` - Main desktop wallpaper
   - `sddm.jpg` - Login screen background
   - `gnome.jpg` - GNOME desktop wallpaper (if using GNOME)

3. Edit `backgrounds.nix`:
   - Comment out the `environment.systemPackages` section
   - Uncomment the `environment.etc` section

4. Your images will be available at:
   - `/etc/backgrounds/default.jpg`
   - `/etc/backgrounds/sddm.jpg`
   - `/etc/backgrounds/gnome.jpg`

## Current Setup:

By default, wallpapers are downloaded from the internet during system build.
This avoids storing large image files in git.